  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in a ttukbaegi earthenware over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for another minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the peanuts and cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring frequently.",
    "Add the hominy, sherry vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper. Mix well.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10-15 minutes.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Garnish with scallions and grated cheese (if using)."
